{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_64","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '20,80p'\"","aggregated_output":"    20\t\n    21\tMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\n    22\t`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\n    23\t\n    24\t- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\n    25\t- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\n    26\t- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\n    27\t- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\n    28\t- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\n    29\t\n    30\tThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\n    31\tso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\n    32\t\n    33\t### Geometry handoff contract\n    34\t\n    35\tMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\n    36\t`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\n    37\tfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\n    38\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\n    39\t\n    40\tPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\n    41\t\n    42\t- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\n    43\t- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\n    44\t- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\n    45\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\n    46\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\n    47\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\n    48\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\n    49\t\n    50\t`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\n    51\tmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\n    52\tstatuses/paths.\n    53\t\n    54\tCompatibility shim:\n    55\t\n    56\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\n    57\t  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\n    58\t  sidecar name during migration.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
